There was a thread about this a couple of months back.  Dont worry
about the low SI rating (Nortons is a shit program to landmark with!)

It is due to the way nortons heavily reply on cache speeds.  If you
have full banks of cache, then the cache will interleave, thus allowing
reads and writes at the "same" time.  Nortons cant figure this out and 
thus falls over.

Your machine will run a bit fasters by using SRAM : FAST but dont 
really worry about it

Paul

